Space Oddity, on the other hand, was much more serious.
On Born In A UFO, David Bowie once again refers to his strangeness: could he come from another planet?
The guitar riffs, the haunting, the earth-shattering.
Bowie has a lot of fun playing the chameleon with these titles: informant in turn, man on a rocket, Martian potential...
