And that shape will be the whole room: a string of physical imitations of the drawings.
The dancers, all dressed in black, only their hands and faces uncovered, wait on either side of the playing field, rush in when the next graffiti appears, embody it, run out.
This black and white game by Henri Michaux is made in relay of solos, in a group in unison (a mass that is solo), in a large group of twelve solos where each one performs his sign.
We think of "Morning Glory", where, solo, Chouinard performed a series of choreographic tasks written on posters, placed in a row in the foreground.
