On stage, couples pass, in couples in love, very sensual, even erotic.
Group work, little solo transitions, moving ensembles, choirs, the writing is less binary.
The clowns, as familiar to Chouinard, appear, sporting the red nose, in highly polarized male-female love parades.
Lovers are carnivorous, fugitive or playful.
The gestures, the laughter and the little cries transpose the archaic, the grace and the ridiculousness of the bodies into coitus, of the beings that merge.
