The French police have decided to impose strict rules regarding the match between Royal Sporting Club of Anderlecht and Paris Saint-Germain scheduled for Tuesday, Marie Verbeke, the spokeswoman for the Brussels-Medi police area, said on Friday.
Belgian RSCA supporters who wish to attend this Champions League match will have to use the travel system set up by the RSCA.
"The bus convoy will be escorted by the police from a former border post in Rekem to the PSG stadium", the spokeswoman said.
